http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Steps-to-ensure-food-safety-during-Pongala/article14026622.ece

The Food Safety Department has taken steps to ensure safety of food items sold through eateries and by those who intend to offer food during the Attukal Pongala festival.Food Safety Commissioner T.V. Anupama in a release said those who wished to open food outlets. Details about registration are available over phone (8943346526) or from any of the Akshaya centres in the city, through which registration was possible.Registration had been made mandatory for offering free food to devotees and opening temporary outlets, the release said.Complaints related to food safety during festivals could be filed by dialling the toll-free number 1800 425 1125 or 89433 41130, 89433 46526,89433 46529,89433 46195.